{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-entry-js","path":"/notes/ml/rec/nonpersonal","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Non-Personalized Methods"},"html":"<h3>Motivating Non-Personalized Recommenders</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>In general, non-personalized recommendations are usually generated for an average user</li>\n<li>Since the average profile is associated with such a small percentage of users, these non-personalized recommendations aren't very useful</li>\n<li>Non-personalized recommendations aren't usually accurate compared to personalized recommendations</li>\n<li>However, they can be useful when we don't have information about certain users (or used in hybrids)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Defining Types of Non-Personalized Recommendations</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Popular Items</strong>: popular categories, brands or products</li>\n<li><strong>New Releases</strong>: new products released</li>\n<li><strong>Similar Items</strong>: similarly purchased products</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Trending Items</strong>: products trending upwards</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Where, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>s</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">s_{1}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is the percentage change in sales for the previous day</li>\n<li>And, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>s</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">s_{2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is the percentage change in sales two days ago</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msub><mi>s</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>0.5</mn><mo>×</mo><msub><mi>s</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">trend(i) = (1 \\times s_{1}) + (0.5 \\times s_{2})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span><span class=\"mord\">5</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">×</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>\n<h3>References</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://algorithmicweb.files.wordpress.com/2018/07/algorithmic-marketing-ai-for-marketing-operations-r1-7g.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Textbook about Algorithmic Marketing</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"ml/rec/nonpersonal","previousSlug":"ml/rec/context","nextSlug":"ml/rec/multiobjective","previousTitle":"Contextual Recommendations","nextTitle":"Multi-Objective Methods"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}